{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn about the new tools in Xcode 9 for exploring the source control history of your projects. See how Xcode integrates with GitHub, and discover how the new source control navigator makes it easy to browse branches, tags, and detailed history and commit information.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions"},{"type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-418-Source-Control-Workflows-in-Xcode","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-403-Whats-New-in-Signing-for-Xcode-and-Xcode-Server","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-404-Debugging-with-Xcode-9","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-409-Whats-New-in-Testing"],"style":"list"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC17","title":"GitHub and the New Source Control Workflows in Xcode 9","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-405-github-and-the-new-source-control-workflows-in-xcode-9"]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/405\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-405-GitHub-and-the-New-Source-Control-Workflows-in-Xcode-9"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","title":"Learn More…","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"text":" and more.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","kind":"article","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC17"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/405/":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/405\/","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/405\/"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-418-Source-Control-Workflows-in-Xcode":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-418-source-control-workflows-in-xcode","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode integrates with GitHub, Bitbucket, and GitLab to help you manage your source code, back up your files, and collaborate with others. Find out how to easily see the changes in your project right in the source editor, and learn how to use Xcode for common source control workflows with Git. See how conflicts occur, how to resolve them, and how to avoid them before they even happen."}],"title":"Source Control Workflows in Xcode","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-418-Source-Control-Workflows-in-Xcode"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-409-Whats-New-in-Testing":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9 has new APIs for structuring your test logging and including your own attachments and screenshots, as well as new support for parallel device and simulator testing. Learn how to write UI tests that target multiple applications, and find out ways to improve the performance of your UI tests."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-409-whats-new-in-testing","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-409-Whats-New-in-Testing","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"What’s New in Testing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-404-Debugging-with-Xcode-9":{"type":"topic","title":"Debugging with Xcode 9","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-404-Debugging-with-Xcode-9","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9 introduces wireless development for iOS and tvOS. Discover how to configure and use wireless development with your devices. Learn about Xcode’s latest debugging features — including debugging workflow enhancements, and new view debugging support for view controllers, SpriteKit and SceneKit — now with no strings attached."}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-404-debugging-with-xcode-9"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-403-Whats-New-in-Signing-for-Xcode-and-Xcode-Server":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-403-Whats-New-in-Signing-for-Xcode-and-Xcode-Server","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Learn about new advances in Xcode’s support for code signing, including more powerful distribution signing, better integration with Xcode Server, and more control for working with manual signing assets.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-403-whats-new-in-signing-for-xcode-and-xcode-server","title":"What’s New in Signing for Xcode and Xcode Server"}}}